"content": "<style>\nh1.thlex-title { font-size: 1.3em; margin: 0 0 0.4em; }\n.thlex-key { color: #888; font-size: 0.85em; font-weight: normal; margin-right: 0.4em; }\nnav.thlex-index { margin: 0.5em 0 0.75em; }\nnav.thlex-index ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2em; }\nnav.thlex-index li { margin: 0.15em 0; font-size: 0.95em; }\n.thlex-section { margin: 0.6em 0; }\nh2.thlex-heading { font-size: 1em; margin: 0.5em 0 0.2em; }\nh3.thlex-subheading { font-size: 0.95em; font-weight: normal; font-style: italic; margin: 0.2em 0; }\n.thlex-language-sets { margin: 0.3em 0 0.3em 1em; }\n.thlex-language-set { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 0.75em; border-left: 3px solid #e0e0e0; }\n.thlex-language { font-size: 0.8em; color: #888; margin-right: 0.4em; }\n.thlex-lemma { font-weight: bold; font-family: serif; }\n.thlex-translit { color: #555; font-style: italic; font-size: 0.9em; margin-left: 0.3em; }\n.thlex-refs { font-size: 0.85em; color: #444; margin-top: 0.15em; }\n.thlex-paragraphs p { margin: 0.35em 0; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.5; }\n.thlex-image { margin: 0.5em 0; display: block; }\n.thlex-image img { max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; }\nfigcaption.thlex-caption { font-size: 0.85em; color: #555; font-style: italic; margin-top: 0.2em; }\n.thlex-abbr { border-bottom: 1px dotted #888; cursor: help; }\n.thlex-xref { color: #1a5fb4; }\nspan[data-bnType=\"bibleReference\"] { color: #1a5fb4; }\ntable.thlex-table { border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.9em; margin: 0.5em 0; }\ntable.thlex-table td { padding: 0.2em 0.6em; vertical-align: top; border: 1px solid #ddd; }\ntable.thlex-table tr:first-child td { font-weight: bold; background: #f5f5f5; }\nul.thlex-index-list { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.6; }\nul.thlex-index-list ul { margin: 0.1em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; }\n.thlex-index-key { font-weight: bold; font-style: italic; }\n</style><h1 class=\"thlex-title\" id=\"REALIA:6.2.1\"><span class=\"thlex-key\">6.2.1</span> Hem, corner of a garment</h1><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">References:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-sets\">\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">כָּנָף</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(kanaf)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num15:38\">NUM 15:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num15:38\">NUM 15:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut22:12\">DEU 22:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut23:1\">DEU 23:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut27:20\">DEU 27:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth3:9\">RUT 3:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam15:27\">1SA 15:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam24:6\">1SA 24:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam24:12\">1SA 24:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam24:12\">1SA 24:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer2:34\">JER 2:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek5:3\">EZK 5:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek16:8\">EZK 16:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hag2:12\">HAG 2:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hag2:12\">HAG 2:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech8:23\">ZEC 8:23</a></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">Description:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>\n            <figure class=\"thlex-image\"><img class=\"thlex-img\" src=\"images/OAI-0007_pharisee_en.png\" alt=\"A Pharisee, wearing phylactery and prayer shawl\"><figcaption class=\"thlex-caption\">A Pharisee, wearing phylactery and prayer shawl (Image generated by ChatGPT using OpenAI technology)</figcaption></figure>The hem was the lower edge of an outer garment (see <a class=\"thlex-xref\" data-bnType=\"lexiconLink\" data-collection=\"\" data-key=\"\" href=\"#\">6.2 Outer garment, cloak, mantle, robe&lt;REALIA:6.2&gt;</a>).</p>\n<hr/>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">Usage:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>See <a class=\"thlex-xref\" data-bnType=\"lexiconLink\" data-collection=\"\" data-key=\"\" href=\"#\">6.2.1.1 Fringe, tassel&lt;REALIA:6.2.1.1&gt;</a>.</p>\n<hr/>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">Translation:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>Most translations render the Hebrew word <em>kanaf</em> in <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num15:38\">NUM 15:38</a> and <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut22:12\">DEU 22:12</a> as “corners” (<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Revised Standard Version (1952)\">RSV</abbr>, <abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Good News Translation (1992)\">GNT</abbr>). In <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num15:38\">NUM 15:38</a><abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Contemporary English Version\">CEV</abbr> says “bottom edge,” which may also serve as a model.</p>\n<p>\n            <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech8:23\">ZEC 8:23</a>: While the word <em>kanaf</em> indicates the lower edge of a garment, it is sometimes used for the garment itself (compare <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer2:34\">JER 2:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek16:8\">EZK 16:8</a>). In such passages it may be possible to use a word for the outer garment. Two models for the first part of <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech8:23\">ZEC 8:23</a> are “When this happens, ten people from nations with different languages will grab a Jew by his clothes” (<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Contemporary English Version\">CEV</abbr>) and “At that time, ten men from different countries will come and take hold of a Judean by his coat” (<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"New Century Version\">NCV</abbr>). <abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Good News Translation (1992)\">GNT</abbr> “In those days ten foreigners will come to one Jew” is also possible, although it loses the element of urgency conveyed by the act of grabbing hold of the robe.</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
