"content": "<style>\nh1.thlex-title { font-size: 1.3em; margin: 0 0 0.4em; }\n.thlex-key { color: #888; font-size: 0.85em; font-weight: normal; margin-right: 0.4em; }\nnav.thlex-index { margin: 0.5em 0 0.75em; }\nnav.thlex-index ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2em; }\nnav.thlex-index li { margin: 0.15em 0; font-size: 0.95em; }\n.thlex-section { margin: 0.6em 0; }\nh2.thlex-heading { font-size: 1em; margin: 0.5em 0 0.2em; }\nh3.thlex-subheading { font-size: 0.95em; font-weight: normal; font-style: italic; margin: 0.2em 0; }\n.thlex-language-sets { margin: 0.3em 0 0.3em 1em; }\n.thlex-language-set { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 0.75em; border-left: 3px solid #e0e0e0; }\n.thlex-language { font-size: 0.8em; color: #888; margin-right: 0.4em; }\n.thlex-lemma { font-weight: bold; font-family: serif; }\n.thlex-translit { color: #555; font-style: italic; font-size: 0.9em; margin-left: 0.3em; }\n.thlex-refs { font-size: 0.85em; color: #444; margin-top: 0.15em; }\n.thlex-paragraphs p { margin: 0.35em 0; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.5; }\n.thlex-image { margin: 0.5em 0; display: block; }\n.thlex-image img { max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; }\nfigcaption.thlex-caption { font-size: 0.85em; color: #555; font-style: italic; margin-top: 0.2em; }\n.thlex-abbr { border-bottom: 1px dotted #888; cursor: help; }\n.thlex-xref { color: #1a5fb4; }\nspan[data-bnType=\"bibleReference\"] { color: #1a5fb4; }\ntable.thlex-table { border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.9em; margin: 0.5em 0; }\ntable.thlex-table td { padding: 0.2em 0.6em; vertical-align: top; border: 1px solid #ddd; }\ntable.thlex-table tr:first-child td { font-weight: bold; background: #f5f5f5; }\nul.thlex-index-list { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.6; }\nul.thlex-index-list ul { margin: 0.1em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; }\n.thlex-index-key { font-weight: bold; font-style: italic; }\n</style><h1 class=\"thlex-title\" id=\"REALIA:6.2.1.1\"><span class=\"thlex-key\">6.2.1.1</span> Fringe, tassel</h1><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">References:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-sets\">\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">צִיצִת</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(tsitsith)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num15:38\">NUM 15:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num15:38\">NUM 15:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num15:39\">NUM 15:39</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">גָּדִל</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(gadil)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut22:12\">DEU 22:12</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">κράσπεδον</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(kraspedon)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:20\">MAT 9:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt14:36\">MAT 14:36</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt23:5\">MAT 23:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:56\">MRK 6:56</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:44\">LUK 8:44</a></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">Description:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>\n            <figure class=\"thlex-image\"><img class=\"thlex-img\" src=\"images/WEB-0501_fringe_en.jpg\" alt=\"Fringes on a prayer shawl\"><figcaption class=\"thlex-caption\">Fringes on a prayer shawl (DRosenbach, Public domain, via Wikimedia Commons)</figcaption></figure>The decorative tassel was attached to the bottom edge of a long, outer robe, specifically to one of the robe’s four corners.</p>\n<hr/>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">Usage:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>According to <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num15:37-Num15:41\">NUM 15:37–NUM 15:41</a> and <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut22:12\">DEU 22:12</a>, Israelite men were required to wear tassels on the four corners of their outer garments (see <a class=\"thlex-xref\" data-bnType=\"lexiconLink\" data-collection=\"\" data-key=\"\" href=\"#\">6.1 Clothing (generic)&lt;REALIA:6.1&gt;</a>). These tassels reminded them of their obligation to keep the commandments of the Mosaic Law.</p>\n<hr/>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">Translation:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>In <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt23:5\">MAT 23:5</a> the Greek word <em>kraspedon</em> refers to the tassels worn at the four corners of outer garments. It is also possible that in all instances in which <em>kraspedon</em> is used in reference to Jesus’ clothing (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:20\">MAT 9:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt14:36\">MAT 14:36</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:56\">MRK 6:56</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:44\">LUK 8:44</a>), the reference may be specifically to the tassels and not merely to the edge of his garment. The interpretation of such passages depends upon how Jesus may have understood and followed the Mosaic Law and the manner in which the authors may have understood the meaning of <em>kraspedon</em>.</p>\n<p>In some languages the literal phrase “tassels on the corners” (<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Revised Standard Version (1952)\">RSV</abbr>) in <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num15:38\">NUM 15:38</a> may be rendered “decorated corners” or “ribbons at the corners.” Where a word for tassel does not exist or would be obscure, translators may use a descriptive phrase; for example, <abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"New Century Version\">NCV</abbr> renders the second clause of this verse as follows: “Tie several pieces of thread together and attach them to the corners of your clothes.”</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
